(power_switching, time).explanation: Power switching consumption and execution time are independent metrics where switching power represents energy consumed during transistor state changes while execution time measures performance;

(power_switching, power_clock).explanation: Both switching power and clock power are separate components of total processor power consumption that operate independently in the power breakdown hierarchy;

(power_switching, area_net_area).explanation: Switching power consumption and net area are independent metrics where power represents dynamic energy usage while net area is a physical design constraint;
